      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JUST BELIEVE (6) has been a little hard to follow, finishing out of the placings latest but was in winning form two back scoring in a Grade 5 at this track. Meets a moderate line up and rates on top this time. SPECIAL LAD (2) has missed the frame the last couple but was a Grade 5 winner three back (22.23) at Shepparton over 390m. Can feature with the right run. BIG MAKO (3) missed the frame and was safely held latest finishing 7th at this track following on from a third place finish (22.83) there the start prior. Solid record here at the distance winning five races. Better than last start and can bounce back. AUSSIE WAGYU (4) scored last time and appeals as a top-three prospect.",
